CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782821899
OL,3,CPeston: Is it president Burnham?
OL,5,FThis is redolent of French or American
OL,6,Fseparation of presidential/executive,
OL,7,Fparliamentary and state/municipal
OL,8,Fpowers more than the British tradition.
OL,10,FIt may be a good thing. It may be the
OL,11,Fessential narrowing of the wealth and
OL,12,Fincome gaps between London/south-east
OL,13,Fand the rest of the UK.
OL,15,FBut we do not have a directly elected
OL,16,Fpresident. And even if this kind of
OL,17,Fconstitutional change bores you to
OL,18,Ftears, it matters: we've had a
OL,19,Fparliamentary system that has muddled
OL,20,Fthrough for 250 years, give or take.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
