OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782821899
OL,3,CPeston: Is it president Burnham?
OL,5,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,6,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,7,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,8,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,10,FAlthough it may make very good sense
OL,11,Fto end the near absolute power of
OL,12,Fcentralising Westminster departments
OL,13,Fand their often over-confident
OL,14,Fsecretaries of state, while
OL,15,Ftransferring vital economic decisions
OL,16,Fto elected mayors or councillors who
OL,17,Fknow what their communities actually
OL,18,Fneed, it is not so conspicuously the
OL,19,Fcase that MPs themselves need cutting
OL,20,Fdown to size.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782821899
OL,3,CPeston: Is it president Burnham?
OL,5,FThey should think hard about what kind
OL,6,Fof role they want in this new system
OL,7,Fof newly distributed power.
OL,9,FThere is a case for saying they - in
OL,10,Fsome kind of British version of
OL,11,FAmerican confessional committees -
OL,12,Fshould have more oversight over
OL,13,FBurnham's much expanded Office of the
OL,14,Fprime minister, mayors and economic
OL,15,Fregulators.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782821899
OL,3,CPeston: Is it president Burnham?
OL,5,FIf they don't hold the new quasi
OL,6,Fpresidential system to account, who
OL,7,Fwould - especially when so much of
OL,8,FBurnham's personal authority will flow
OL,9,Ffrom a presidential style of talking
OL,10,Fto and directly connecting with voters?
OL,12,FWhich brings me to the Boris Johnson
OL,13,Fechoes.
OL,15,FThey are that.
OL,17,FFirst, Tory MPs saw him - just as
OL,18,FLabour MPs see Burnham - as some kind
OL,19,Fof election winning messiah.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782821899
OL,3,CPeston: Is it president Burnham?
OL,5,FSecond, Johnson talked an incessant
OL,6,Ftalk of narrowing the gap between
OL,7,Fnorth and south, which he called
OL,8,F"levelling up", his version of
OL,9,FBurnham's "Manchesterism" - but no
OL,10,Fserious transfer of decision making to
OL,11,Flocal people ever accompanied
OL,12,F"levelling up", and most would say it
OL,13,Fwas hot air.
OL,15,FThird, Johnson - like Burnham -
OL,16,Fexploited his figurehead status as a
OL,17,Fformer mayor, his popularity and a
OL,18,Fpersonal connection with voters that
OL,19,Fhe ruthlessly cultivated.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@NO]qD@KOUqD@YO]tD@AOUtD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
